  "text": "In fact, the two-layer regrasp graph [CITATION_1] is similar to ours. One major difference is that they did not exploit any grasp parameterization in building the graph. Therefore, in their case, each grasp class contains exactly one grasp, hence numerous grasp classes. Also, the deterministic search employed in DBMP makes its capability relatively limited. Firstly, all placements have to be constrained to only one location on the table, or at most a few, due to time complexity of the search. Second, a significant amount of time is spent on exploring infeasible placement and grasp sequences due to the depth-first fashion of the search. This makes the success rate of DBMP in the given time much lower than the other planners.",
